The Prime Minister headed to Riyadh this morning to beg Crown Prince Mohammed Bin Salman to increase oil production to the West as it weans itself off Russian oil. Mr Johnson's controversial trip is likely to dominate the conversation as the Government faces criticism over the Saudi Government's human rights record. On Saturday, 81 people were executed in one day for opposing the regime. The PM defended the trip calling it a "very important relationship". FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 